[~ethomas] Running "euca-modify-property -p cloud.euca_log_level=DEBUG"  immediately after running esi-manage-stack -a create/delete imaging does in fact cause the stack process to hang. The only way to recover is to manually delete the stack information from the database and reset euca-modify-property -p services.imaging.worker.configured=false.
It appears that Vic added the DEBUG log level change recently to the QA system exposing this issue.

To Reproduce:
{code}
1) On QA faststart machine that has already run you must clean database from of failed stack and reset image worker property
  a) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stacks;
  b) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stack_events;
  c) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stack_resources;
  d) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stack_workflows;
  e) euca-modify-property -p services.imaging.worker.configured=false

2) Run script  /usr/bin/esi-manage-stack -a create imaging"

3) immediately followed by euca-modify-property -p cloud.euca_log_level=$DIFFERENT_LOG_LEVEL

4) check stack by assuming imaging_acct:role:
    export imaging_acct=`euare-accountlist | grep imaging | awk '{print $2}'`  && eval `euare-assumerole arn:aws:iam::$imaging_acct:role/imaging/ImagingServiceAdministrator --region localhost`
 
5) Check stack events: euform-describe-stack-events euca-internal-imaging-service

6) you will notice that the stack gets stuck "in progress" and never completes.
{code}

I am currently looking at how to fix this.

The issue is that polling for workflows with pending decision tasks uses an example object that does not clear the state related properties, we should change:

{code}
    workflowExecution.setState( ExecutionStatus.Open );
{code}

to:

{code}
    workflowExecution.setState( ExecutionStatus.Open );
    workflowExecution.setStateChangeStack( null );
    workflowExecution.setLastState( null );
{code}

in WorkflowExecution#exampleWithPendingDecision to address the issue. 

When DEBUG or lower level is used the stateChangeStack will be set to an empty string, in INFO or higher levels the stateChangeStack will be "n/a", this causes polling for workflow executions with pending tasks to find nothing when the log level at query time differs from the log level in use when the workflow execution (stack) was created.

This is a small fix with low regression potential and may be suitable for 4.2 as the current behaviour would cause issues for cloudformation users.

[~swathi] Here are the steps to reproduce:
{code}
1) On QA faststart machine that has already run "esi-manage-stack -a create imaging" and failed  you must clean database from of failed stack and reset image worker property
  a) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stacks;
  b) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stack_events;
  c) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stack_resources;
  d) delete from eucalyptus_cloudformation.stack_workflows;
  e) euca-modify-property -p services.imaging.worker.configured=false
  
  If this has not already failed you can go to step 2)

2) Run script  /usr/bin/esi-manage-stack -a create imaging"

3) immediately followed by euca-modify-property -p cloud.euca_log_level=$DIFFERENT_LOG_LEVEL (DEBUG or Greater)

4) check stack by assuming imaging_acct:role:
    export imaging_acct=`euare-accountlist | grep imaging | awk '{print $2}'`  && eval `euare-assumerole arn:aws:iam::$imaging_acct:role/imaging/ImagingServiceAdministrator --region localhost`
 
5) Check stack events: euform-describe-stack-events euca-internal-imaging-service

6) you will notice that the stack gets stuck "in progress" and never completes.
{code}

With the fix you will see the stack creation complete even with the log level change.
